message.content:
We first calculate the average owner's equity using the beginning and ending amounts. Note that the Owner’s Equity in the balance sheet is given as follows:

• Beginning Owner’s Equity = 13,000,000.00  
• Ending Owner’s Equity = 13,963,263.19

Step 1. Compute the average owner's equity:  
  Average Owner’s Equity = (Beginning + Ending) / 2  
    = (13,000,000.00 + 13,963,263.19) / 2  
    = 26,963,263.19 / 2  
    = 13,481,631.595

Step 2. Identify the Net Profit from the income statement:  
  Net Profit = 963,263.19

Step 3. Calculate ROE using the formula:  
  ROE = (Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity) × 100%  
  ROE = (963,263.19 / 13,481,631.595) × 100%  
  ROE ≈ 7.14%

Thus, the Return on Equity (ROE) is approximately 7.14%.
